### Seval Ata
**In this homework, we are going to use the English Premier Lig data. At the beginning, I have prepared the data as a data table and add necessary columns for the tasks.**
*necessary libraries*

library(lubridate)
library(data.table)
library(ggplot2)
library(gridExtra)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
*loading the data and turning them into data table format*

matches_file_path="/Users/Seval/Desktop/Dersler/IE582/HW1-2019/matches.csv"
matches=read.csv(matches_file_path)
bets_file_path="/Users/Seval/Desktop/Dersler/IE582/HW1-2019/bets.csv"
bets=read.csv(bets_file_path)
booking_file_path="/Users/Seval/Desktop/Dersler/IE582/HW1-2019/booking.csv"
booking=read.csv(booking_file_path)
goals_file_path="/Users/Seval/Desktop/Dersler/IE582/HW1-2019/goals.csv"
goals=read.csv(goals_file_path)
stats_file_path="/Users/Seval/Desktop/Dersler/IE582/HW1-2019/stats.csv"
stats=read.csv(stats_file_path)

matchesdt=data.table(matches)
betsdt=data.table(bets)
bookingdt=data.table(booking)
goalsdt=data.table(goals)
statsdt=data.table(stats)

*adding new column to the data: difference_of_scores*
*filtering the data for only English Premier League data
removing the matches that are not finished yet*

matchesdt$match_hometeam_score=as.numeric(matchesdt$match_hometeam_score)
matchesdt$match_awayteam_score=as.numeric(matchesdt$match_awayteam_score)
matchesdt[,difference_of_scores:=match_hometeam_score-match_awayteam_score]
matchesdtEPL=matchesdt[league_id==148]
matchesdtEPL=matchesdtEPL[!match_status=="NA"]
# Task 1
In this task we are going to analyze the distribution of the data. Therefore, I prepared the following histograms for Home Scores, Away Scores and the difference of them.
## Part 1

text/plain: Plot with title “Histogram of Home Scores”

source: hist(matchesdtEPL$match_hometeam_score, breaks=16, xlab="Home Goals", ylab= "Number of Games",main="Histogram of Home Scores",col="blue")

text/plain: Plot with title “Histogram of Away Scores”

source: hist(matchesdtEPL$match_awayteam_score, breaks=12, xlab="Away Goals", ylab= "Number of Games",main="Histogram of Away Scores", col="red")

source: hist(matchesdtEPL$difference_of_scores,xlab="Home Goals-Away Goals", ylab= "Number of Games",main="Histogram of Home Scores-Away Scores", col="green")
## Part 2

text/plain: Plot with title “Histogram of Home Scores with Poisson Pdf”

source:
h1<-hist(matchesdtEPL$match_hometeam_score,breaks=16,xlab="Home Goals", ylab= "Number of Games",main="Histogram of Home Scores with Poisson Pdf", col="blue")
xhist1<-c(min(h1$breaks),h1$breaks)
yhist1<-c(0,h1$density,0)
xfit1<-seq(min(matchesdtEPL$match_hometeam_score),max(matchesdtEPL$match_hometeam_score),by=1) 
yfit1<-dpois(xfit1,lambda=mean(matchesdtEPL$match_hometeam_score), log=FALSE) 
yfit1 <- yfit1*diff(h1$mids[1:2])*length(matchesdtEPL$match_hometeam_score) 
lines(xfit1, yfit1, col="black", lwd=3)

text/plain: Plot with title “Histogram of Away Scores with Poisson Pdf”

source:
h2<-hist(matchesdtEPL$match_awayteam_score,breaks=12,xlab="Away Goals", ylab= "Number of Games",main="Histogram of Away Scores with Poisson Pdf", col="red")
xhist2<-c(min(h2$breaks),h2$breaks)
yhist2<-c(0,h2$density,0)
xfit2<-seq(min(matchesdtEPL$match_awayteam_score),max(matchesdtEPL$match_awayteam_score),by=1) 
yfit2<-dpois(xfit2,lambda=mean(matchesdtEPL$match_awayteam_score), log=FALSE) 
yfit2 <- yfit2*diff(h2$mids[1:2])*length(matchesdtEPL$match_awayteam_score) 
lines(xfit2, yfit2, col="black", lwd=3)
**When we compare the actual and theoretical distribution in those plots, we can conclude that the both of the distributions look like fitting well to Poisson distribution.**
# Task 2
The aim of this task is to understand if bookmakers are good enough in setting their odds for “draw” bets.
I selected the following 4 bookmakers for this task: **1xBet, Marathonbet, BetVictor, Betclic.**
*adding a new column as IsDraw to indicate whether a match is finished as tie or not*
matchesdtEPL[,IsDraw:=0]
matchesdtEPL[match_hometeam_score==match_awayteam_score,IsDraw:=1]
*merging bets and matches data and calculating probability of home win, away win or draw probability as 1/odd*
merged_matches_bets=merge(matchesdtEPL,betsdt,by='match_id')
merged_matches_bets=merged_matches_bets[,probability:=1/value]
*separating the bookmakers' data*

merged_matches_bets_1xBet=merged_matches_bets[odd_bookmakers=="1xBet"]
merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet=merged_matches_bets[odd_bookmakers=="Marathonbet"]
merged_matches_bets_BetVictor=merged_matches_bets[odd_bookmakers=="BetVictor"]
merged_matches_bets_Betclic=merged_matches_bets[odd_bookmakers=="Betclic"]
*separating the home-win, draw and away-win data of each bookmakers*

merged_matches_bets_1xBet_homewin=merged_matches_bets_1xBet[variable=="odd_1"]
merged_matches_bets_1xBet_draw=merged_matches_bets_1xBet[variable=="odd_x"]
merged_matches_bets_1xBet_awaywin=merged_matches_bets_1xBet[variable=="odd_2"]

merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet_homewin=merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet[variable=="odd_1"]
merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet_draw=merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet[variable=="odd_x"]
merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet_awaywin=merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet[variable=="odd_2"]

merged_matches_bets_BetVictor_homewin=merged_matches_bets_BetVictor[variable=="odd_1"]
merged_matches_bets_BetVictor_draw=merged_matches_bets_BetVictor[variable=="odd_x"]
merged_matches_bets_BetVictor_awaywin=merged_matches_bets_BetVictor[variable=="odd_2"]

merged_matches_bets_Betclic_homewin=merged_matches_bets_Betclic[variable=="odd_1"]
merged_matches_bets_Betclic_draw=merged_matches_bets_Betclic[variable=="odd_x"]
merged_matches_bets_Betclic_awaywin=merged_matches_bets_Betclic[variable=="odd_2"]
*adding home-win, draw and away-win probabilities of the every matches given by four bookmakers as the new columns*

merged_1xBet=merged_matches_bets_1xBet_homewin
names(merged_1xBet)[24]="home_win_probability"
merged_1xBet$draw_probability<-NA
merged_1xBet$draw_probability<-merged_matches_bets_1xBet_draw$probability
merged_1xBet$away_win_probability<-NA
merged_1xBet$away_win_probability<-merged_matches_bets_1xBet_awaywin$probability

merged_Marathonbet=merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet_homewin
names(merged_Marathonbet)[24]="home_win_probability"
merged_Marathonbet$draw_probability<-NA
merged_Marathonbet$draw_probability<-merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet_draw$probability
merged_Marathonbet$away_win_probability<-NA
merged_Marathonbet$away_win_probability<-merged_matches_bets_Marathonbet_awaywin$probability

merged_BetVictor=merged_matches_bets_BetVictor_homewin
names(merged_BetVictor)[24]="home_win_probability"
merged_BetVictor$draw_probability<-NA
merged_BetVictor$draw_probability<-merged_matches_bets_BetVictor_draw$probability
merged_BetVictor$away_win_probability<-NA
merged_BetVictor$away_win_probability<-merged_matches_bets_BetVictor_awaywin$probability

merged_Betclic=merged_matches_bets_Betclic_homewin
names(merged_Betclic)[24]="home_win_probability"
merged_Betclic$draw_probability<-NA
merged_Betclic$draw_probability<-merged_matches_bets_Betclic_draw$probability
merged_Betclic$away_win_probability<-NA
merged_Betclic$away_win_probability<-merged_matches_bets_Betclic_awaywin$probability
*calculating the home-win, draw and away-win probabilities again by normalization*

merged_1xBet=merged_1xBet[,implied_home_win_probability:=merged_1xBet$home_win_probability/(merged_1xBet$home_win_probability+merged_1xBet$draw_probability+merged_1xBet$away_win_probability)]
merged_1xBet=merged_1xBet[,implied_draw_probability:=merged_1xBet$draw_probability/(merged_1xBet$home_win_probability+merged_1xBet$draw_probability+merged_1xBet$away_win_probability)]
merged_1xBet=merged_1xBet[,implied_away_win_probability:=merged_1xBet$away_win_probability/(merged_1xBet$home_win_probability+merged_1xBet$draw_probability+merged_1xBet$away_win_probability)]
merged_1xBet=merged_1xBet[,p_home_minus_p_away:=home_win_probability-away_win_probability]

merged_Marathonbet=merged_Marathonbet[,implied_home_win_probability:=merged_Marathonbet$home_win_probability/(merged_Marathonbet$home_win_probability+merged_Marathonbet$draw_probability+merged_Marathonbet$away_win_probability)]
merged_Marathonbet=merged_Marathonbet[,implied_draw_probability:=merged_Marathonbet$draw_probability/(merged_Marathonbet$home_win_probability+merged_Marathonbet$draw_probability+merged_Marathonbet$away_win_probability)]
merged_Marathonbet=merged_Marathonbet[,implied_away_win_probability:=merged_Marathonbet$away_win_probability/(merged_Marathonbet$home_win_probability+merged_Marathonbet$draw_probability+merged_Marathonbet$away_win_probability)]
merged_Marathonbet=merged_Marathonbet[,p_home_minus_p_away:=home_win_probability-away_win_probability]

merged_BetVictor=merged_BetVictor[,implied_home_win_probability:=merged_BetVictor$home_win_probability/(merged_BetVictor$home_win_probability+merged_BetVictor$draw_probability+merged_BetVictor$away_win_probability)]
merged_BetVictor=merged_BetVictor[,implied_draw_probability:=merged_BetVictor$draw_probability/(merged_BetVictor$home_win_probability+merged_BetVictor$draw_probability+merged_BetVictor$away_win_probability)]
merged_BetVictor=merged_BetVictor[,implied_away_win_probability:=merged_BetVictor$away_win_probability/(merged_BetVictor$home_win_probability+merged_BetVictor$draw_probability+merged_BetVictor$away_win_probability)]
merged_BetVictor=merged_BetVictor[,p_home_minus_p_away:=home_win_probability-away_win_probability]

merged_Betclic=merged_Betclic[,implied_home_win_probability:=merged_Betclic$home_win_probability/(merged_Betclic$home_win_probability+merged_Betclic$draw_probability+merged_Betclic$away_win_probability)]
merged_Betclic=merged_Betclic[,implied_draw_probability:=merged_Betclic$draw_probability/(merged_Betclic$home_win_probability+merged_Betclic$draw_probability+merged_Betclic$away_win_probability)]
merged_Betclic=merged_Betclic[,implied_away_win_probability:=merged_Betclic$away_win_probability/(merged_Betclic$home_win_probability+merged_Betclic$draw_probability+merged_Betclic$away_win_probability)]
merged_Betclic=merged_Betclic[,p_home_minus_p_away:=home_win_probability-away_win_probability]
*ordering the data according to P(home win)-P(away win)*

merged_1xBet=merged_1xBet[order(p_home_minus_p_away)]
merged_Marathonbet=merged_Marathonbet[order(p_home_minus_p_away)]
merged_BetVictor=merged_BetVictor[order(p_home_minus_p_away)]
merged_Betclic=merged_Betclic[order(p_home_minus_p_away)]
*discretizing P(home win) – P(away win) values into bins*

cutpoints=seq(-1,1,0.2)
merged_1xBet[,cut_probability_diff:=cut(p_home_minus_p_away,cutpoints)]
merged_Marathonbet[,cut_probability_diff:=cut(p_home_minus_p_away,cutpoints)]
merged_BetVictor[,cut_probability_diff:=cut(p_home_minus_p_away,cutpoints)]
merged_Betclic[,cut_probability_diff:=cut(p_home_minus_p_away,cutpoints)]
*calculating the estimated probability of draws*

summary_table1=merged_1xBet[,list(empirical_draw=mean(IsDraw),
                                   probabilistic_draw=mean(p_home_minus_p_away),.N),
                             by=list(cut_probability_diff)]

summary_table2=merged_Marathonbet[,list(empirical_draw=mean(IsDraw),
                                   probabilistic_draw=mean(p_home_minus_p_away),.N),
                             by=list(cut_probability_diff)]

summary_table3=merged_BetVictor[,list(empirical_draw=mean(IsDraw),
                                   probabilistic_draw=mean(p_home_minus_p_away),.N),
                             by=list(cut_probability_diff)]

summary_table4=merged_Betclic[,list(empirical_draw=mean(IsDraw),
                                   probabilistic_draw=mean(p_home_minus_p_away),.N),
                             by=list(cut_probability_diff)]

**Plot of P(home win) – P(away win) on x-axis and P (draw) on y-axis with first probability calculation for each bookmaker is given below. The black points show the individual data, and the blue line shows the trend line. The actual probabilities which are calculated using the results are added to the plot as the colored points.**

plot1=ggplot(merged_1xBet, aes(x=p_home_minus_p_away,y=draw_probability)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth() + ggtitle("1xBet") +
xlab("P(home)-P(away)") + ylab("P(draw)")+ theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, face="bold", size = 16))
plot1= plot1 +geom_point(summary_table1, mapping = aes(x=probabilistic_draw, y=empirical_draw), colour="red")
plot1

xlab("P(home)-P(away)") + ylab("P(draw)")+ theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, face="bold", size = 16))
plot2= plot2 +geom_point(summary_table2, mapping = aes(x=probabilistic_draw, y=empirical_draw), colour="purple")

xlab("P(home)-P(away)") + ylab("P(draw)")+ theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, face="bold", size = 16))
plot3= plot3 +geom_point(summary_table3, mapping = aes(x=probabilistic_draw, y=empirical_draw), colour="orange")
plot3

xlab("P(home)-P(away)") + ylab("P(draw)")+ theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5, face="bold", size = 16))
plot4= plot4 +geom_point(summary_table4, mapping = aes(x=probabilistic_draw, y=empirical_draw), colour="green")
plot4

**We can see that many of the bins for even games, where P(home) − P(away) ≈ 0, are below the odds trend line. Therefore, we can conclude that one is not expected to make money in the long run by betting on “Draw” for the games whose odds reside in the corresponding bin.**
# Task 3

In this task, I am going to eliminate the matches with two cases as following:
- Case 1: matches when a red card is given in the first 30 minutes
- Case 2: matches when a team wins with a goal or goals after 90th minute or match ends draw or away because of the same reason
*adding the columns of both goals and bookings data to the existing data*
merged_1xBet_revised=merge(merged_1xBet,goalsdt,by='match_id')
merged_1xBet_revised=merge(merged_1xBet_revised,bookingdt,by='match_id')
*renaming the name of time variables coming from two different data to get rid of the confusion*
names(merged_1xBet_revised)[32]<-"goal_time"
names(merged_1xBet_revised)[36]<-"card_time"
*separating the time of the goal variable into normal time and extra time for the data in a format such as 90+3 or 45+1*
